Zookeeper start command:
docker run --name zoocontainer -p 2181:2181 zookeeper

Kafka start command from piyush tut:
docker run -d --name kafcontainer \
  -p 9092:9092 \
  -e KAFKA_PROCESS_ROLES='broker' \
  -e KAFKA_BROKER_ID=1 \
  -e KAFKA_ZOOKEEPER_CONNECT='10.99.138.3:2181' \
  -e KAFKA_LISTENER_SECURITY_PROTOCOL_MAP='PLAINTEXT:PLAINTEXT' \
  -e KAFKA_ADVERTISED_LISTENERS='PLAINTEXT://10.99.138.3:9092' \
  -e KAFKA_OFFSETS_TOPIC_REPLICATION_FACTOR=1 \
  -e KAFKA_GROUP_INITIAL_REBALANCE_DELAY_MS=0 \
  -e KAFKA_TRANSACTION_STATE_LOG_REPLICATION_FACTOR=1 \
  -e KAFKA_TRANSACTION_STATE_LOG_MIN_ISR=1 \
  -e KAFKA_JMX_PORT=9101 \
  -e KAFKA_JMX_HOSTNAME=localhost \
  -e KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID='YOUR_GENERATED_CLUSTER_ID' \
  confluentinc/cp-kafka

Kafka start command which actually spins up the kafka container:
docker run --name kafcontainer -p 9092:9092 \
 --link zoocontainer:zookeeper \
 -e KAFKA_ZOOKEEPER_CONNECT=zoocontainer:2181 \
 -e KAFKA_LISTENERS=PLAINTEXT://0.0.0.0:9092 \
 -e KAFKA_ADVERTISED_LISTENERS=PLAINTEXT://localhost:9092 \
 -e KAFKA_BROKER_ID=1 \
 wurstmeister/kafka:latest

// Generated KAFKA_CLUSTER_ID: (No longer needed)
// SFXThAZ2RASawtbdRY0qKg
